items.name: The Electric Badge-aloo
items.item_description: This badge's monocle lets you know it can't see, the cane tells you it's at death's door, and the top hat says it's rich! Marry this badge before some other gold digger snaps it up!

items.name: Modest Metal Pile of Scrap
items.item_description: This humble hat pile of one tells the world that there are more important things in life than money. Like for instance not having any.

items.name: Letch's LED
items.item_description: Comes with x-ray specs that let you see through people's clothes while alerting them with a siren and shouted warnings that you're doing it. Great for prison aficionados who want to go to jail but don't know how.

items.name: The Galvanized Gibus
items.item_description: Elegant simplicity and old-world charm combine with the intoxicating aromas of methyl alcohol and gasoline. Do not wear in unventilated areas.

items.name: Soldered Sensei
items.item_description: Karate masters WANT you to think there's no belt higher than black. But what if we told you there was a secret metal belt ABOVE black that lets you kick a black belt's ass all over the place? Scared black belt guys have been trying to keep a lid on this for years.

items.name: Shooter's Tin Topi
items.item_description: This safari helmet was welded together from actual blood-spattered scraps of jeeps, rifles, shells and fillings discovered at the mauling sites of previous safaris. Wear it as a constant reminder never to do anything as stupid as go on safari.

items.name: Noble Nickel Amassment of Hats
items.item_description: Some hat towers come from humble beginnings, clawing their way to nobility one hat at a time. Other hat towers, like this one, just have rich dads who are the Chief Business Development Officer at Hewlett Packard.

items.name: Base Metal Billycock
items.item_description: Robo-impersonate your favorite fictional bowler-hatted characters, from Batman's Riddler to Clockwork Orange's Alex to England's Winston Churchill.

items.name: Towering Titanium Pillar of Hats
items.item_description: Asimov's Three Laws of Robotics state that 1. Robots can't harm humans and 2. Robots must obey humans, and 3. This hat looks great.

items.name: The Megapixel Beard
items.item_description: Great for taking pictures of all the sexy make-outs you're going to have now that you've got a robot beard. If there's anything ladies find more irresistible, write in and tell us and we'll bolt it onto this perpetual make-out machine.

items.name: The HDMI Patch
items.item_description: Bundled with a broad selection of eyeball-related movies ("Eyes Wide Shut", "The Hills Have Eyes, Part II" and three more) that your friends can enjoy from the comfort of your face.

items.name: The Bolted Bombardier
items.item_description: Remember that time you met the wisest robot in the world? And tore his beard off and stole his stupid pipe? Because the police are here and they want to talk to you.

items.name: The Titanium Towel
items.item_description: Sure, regular towels work fine for water, but what if you're covered in magnets? What's your regular towel doing for you now? Watching you slowly die of magnetism, that's what.

items.name: The Gridiron Guardian
items.item_description: This helmet commemorates the epic Canadian Robot Football League showdown between Les Montreal Footballiers and their Manitoban rivals the Winnepeg Saskatchewans. Don't believe us? Ask any Canadian!

items.name: Tyrantium Helmet
items.item_description: This hat kicks your ass so hard you'll fly into an alternate dimension where Vikings are robots. Deal with it!

items.name: Battery Canteens
items.item_description: Don't let the name fool you: These aren't actual battery canteens capable of converting stored chemical energy into electrical energy. They're just regular canteens that look identical to your water canteen and are filled with battery acid.

items.name: The FR-0
items.item_description: Own this one-of-a-kind piece of memorabilia from the classic '70s film "Blaxton Hale vs. Black HAL 9000".

items.name: Steel Shako
items.item_description: Combining the sublime pageantry of Tchaikovsky's "Nutcracker" with the bold futurism of Tchaikovsky's "Robot Nutcracker vs. Tarzan".

items.name: The Bot Dogger
items.item_description: It's inevitable that robot hot dog hats will someday become the most popular fashion accessory on the planet. And when they do, everyone will claim they liked them "before they were cool." Thanks to the Bot Dogger, only YOU will be able to prove it.

items.name: Ye Oiled Baker Boy
items.item_description: It's as if this hat fell off the tiny metal head of a dirt-stained urchinbot selling robonewspapers in 1899 Mecha-London, rolled through a time tunnel and into your modern backpack.

items.name: The Scrap Sack
items.item_description: Concerned about your many stalkers going through your garbage while you're at work? Rest easy with the Scrap Sack, which lets you keep an eye on your secret-filled trash at all times.

items.name: The Pure Tin Capotain
items.item_description: Witch-hunting: necessary, but time-consuming. What if we told you you could burn up to five witches a day without lifting a finger? Introducing the Pure Tin Capotain, the greatest time-saving invention since the electric can opener.

items.name: Plumber's Pipe
items.item_description: Learn plumbing by osmosis with this handy Home Plumber's Kit! Comes with pipe, length of wire.

items.name: Teddy Robobelt
items.item_description: This tiny robotic bear used to be the President. Now he lives in your pocket. How could the mighty have fallen so far? [makes drinking gesture] Glug glug wink wink.

attributes.name: counts as assister is some kind of pet this update is going to be awesome

items.name: The Cyborg Stunt Helmet
items.item_description: If you pause that big fight scene in the classic film "Swinging Fists of Future Hercules", you can tell that's not actually famous robot actor Kirk RoboDouglas, but a cyborg stuntman. Support the unsung heroes of the silver-plated screen with this limited edition stunt helmet.

items.name: The Electric Escorter
items.item_description: "And it seems to me you lived your life / with a lightbulb in your head / wishing you had cleaned the hole / as the cephalic tetanus spread."  Elton John (words by Bernie Taupin)

items.name: Full Metal Drill Hat
items.item_description: What is your major malfunction, Private Robot? You had best defrag yourself or I will unscrew your head, access the CPU in your neck and fix your major malfunction!

items.name: The Bolt Boy
items.item_description: That item was originally a make-believe superhero accessory tie-in to an imaginary soft drink enjoyed by a fictional character. Now it's also made of metal. There are so many layers of abstraction going on here even we don't know what to make of it.

items.name: The Metal Slug
items.item_description: They came from outer space. And they came to conquer. It was the perfect space crime. But there's just one problem. YOU. "The Metal Slug". Rated R. This Friday. On your HEAD.

attributes.name: counts as assister is some kind of pet this update is going to be awesome

items.name: The Broadband Bonnet
items.item_description: This brimless bonnet cap comes equipped with a satellite pom-pom that streams up-to-the-minute news relevant to the on-the-go Scotsman (golf scores, whiskey prices, when "Braveheart" is on).

items.name: Bonk Leadwear
items.item_description: In 1792, Italian physicist Alessandro Volta invented the battery by mixing zinc, ammonium chloride and molten salt together. In 1932, American soft drink magnate Theophilus Bonk added sugar to this mixture and invented Bonk Cola.

items.name: The Plug-In Prospector
items.item_description: Robo-future history comes alive! Pretend you're a grizzled, cantankerous robot prospector, drunk on teeny-tiny shots of nano-whiskey in the Olllld Cyber-West during the Great Battery Rush of 3047.

items.name: The Rusty Reaper
items.item_description: Are you the personification of death? Do you need to spraypaint something indoors? This skull-shaped rebreather has you covered.

items.name: Soldier's Sparkplug
items.item_description: Sometimes a cigar is just a cigar. Other times it is a sparkplug. Sometimes it is a boot. The important thing is that you have something in your mouth that is on fire.

items.name: The Bolted Bicorne
items.item_description: One little-known fact about parrots: They WILL peck a hole through a human pirate skull. But they can't peck through solid steel. And if they try? This baby's electrified to the tune of 10,000 volts. Your move, parrots.

items.name: The Timeless Topper
items.item_description: Most hats are made of felt, canvas or other non-durable cloths that decompose after a mere 10,000 years. The Timeless Topper's built for the long haul, with an outer layer of scrap titanium and an inner core of plastic bags, foam cups and disposable diapers.

items.name: The Filamental
items.item_description: Is your Pyro made up of alternating current or direct current? Only your electrician knows for sure!

items.name: The Strontium Stove Pipe
items.item_description: Beep boop! I am Old Railsplitter! Welcome to the Hall of Robopresidents! I did my homework on the back of a shovel! Now I must kill all humans with a shovel because I just now became sentient! Beep boop kill all humans!

items.name: Firewall Helmet
items.item_description: Learn the secret that firefighters guard fiercely: There is no better hat to wear while entering a burning building than a metal hat. Why? The metal will absorb 100% of the heat, leaving your bare skin cool and refreshed, probably.

items.name: Respectless Robo-Glove
items.item_description: When that robot selflessly gave you its hand, it assumed you'd study it to advance the field of prosthetic medicine. Sucker. Hey, everybody check me out! I'm a metal chicken! Beep beep gobble boop!

items.name: Pyro's Boron Beanie
items.item_description: Friends and loved ones will call you stupid for wearing this hat. "Hey, moron!" your mother will say. But they won't think it's so funny when you win the Backwards Swimming competition at the Olympics, and are later stripped of your medal for cheating.

items.name: Halogen Head Lamp
items.item_description: This medical marvel improves on the obsolete doctor's head mirror by replacing the mirror part with a 10,000 watt lamp part that can be seen from space. Peer inside your patients' disease-riddled ears, noses and throats from a safe distance.

items.name: Platinum Pickelhaube
items.item_description: Invented by Nikolai Tesla in any one of his ten million appearances in crappy steampunk fiction, probably.

items.name: The Virus Doctor
items.item_description: Whether you're a 17th century plague doctor, a professional wrestler, or a waiter at a plague-themed family restaurant, this hat lets you look the part while delivering last rites, a Tombstone Piledriver and/or plate after plate of bacon-wrapped jalapeo poppers.

items.name: Texas Tin-Gallon
items.item_description: It's a historical fact that in cowboy times, cloth was hard to come by. Creative cowpokes kept the sun out of their eyes by making hats out of what they had in abundance: sheet-metal trees and bolt cactuses.

items.name: Titanium Tyrolean
items.item_description: Meet the robot apocalypse in style with this puckish number, perfect for infiltrating the sentient mother computer located in the Swiss pavilion at Epcot Center.

items.name: Practitioner's Processing Mask
items.item_description: Fact: 70% of the air you breathe was recently in someone's butt. This handy contraption runs the farty air you live in through a gauntlet of soapy water and potpourri before entering your body.

items.name: Bootleg Base Metal Billycock
items.item_description: Trick your friends into thinking your enormous metal hat is a smaller, different hat. If this was actually illegal it would be the PERFECT CRIME.

items.name: Mecha-Medes
items.item_description: Mecha-Medes first appeared in Archimedes' Flights of Fantasy #314 when Archimedes accidentally fell off a table into a parallel world, met his robot double, ate some seeds, squawked in terror at a half-buried Statue of Liberty, then flew into a patio door.

attributes.name: counts as assister is some kind of pet this update is going to be awesome

items.name: The Tungsten Toque
items.item_description: Commemorate history's greatest robot Canadians with this knitted steel cap. Former Prime Minister Pierre Trudeau! Optimus Prime Minister! Commander Data from the hit CBC drama Deep Space Prince Edward Island!

items.name: The Steam Pipe
items.item_description: Just like steampunk ruined reading, the steampipe destroys the harmless pleasure of smoking by tarting it up with a lot of bolts and dials and Nikolai Teslas. Comes with period-appropriate Gary Oldman Dracula glasses!

items.name: The Data Mining Light
items.item_description: If you're a rugged coal miner like us, you know the value of throwing away your mining equipment and mining in the nude so people know how tough you are. Finally there's a version for the office worker to not wear while nudely analyzing spreadsheets.

items.name: The Byte'd Beak
items.item_description: This 17th century plague mask has been upgraded for modern day masquerade-style sex parties with a built-in camera, night vision (for dimly-lit sex parties!) and state-of-the-art sex detection radar.

items.name: The Googol Glass Eyes
items.item_description: These digital eye implants will let you check the weather, monitor the stock market and look up cures for infection caused by jamming unclean hunks of metal into your eye sockets.

items.name: The Bunsen Brave
items.item_description: Scientists have long been baffled by the seamless metal construction of Native American grass houses and wigwams. The secret? Native Americans were filled with gasoline, and could reach a welding flame temperature of 3100 C.

items.name: The Scrumpy Strongbox
items.item_description: This nitrogen-cooled liquor locker can only be opened by punching in its constantly evolving polyalphabetic stream cipher, or with the big metal key scotch taped to the bottom.

items.name: The Dual-Core Devil Doll
items.item_description: These pint-sized pain proxies combine the erotic mysticism of Haitian voodoo with the stultifying boredom of math.

items.name: The Bolted Birdcage
items.item_description: You love the hard-hitting Robin Williams/Nathan Lane bird prison drama "The Birdcage" so much you wish you could be thinking about it all the time. The problem: Life's many distractions. The solution: This.

items.name: The Crosslinker's Coil
items.item_description: Did you know: before the mercenary fashion world discovered the obvious style and mental health benefits of wearing 22 feet of powered electrical cable around your head, people once wore hatbands made from 'silk' or other barely-lethal textiles! Strange but true.

items.name: The Beastly Bonnet
items.item_description: This ceremonial headdress tells your enemies that you have the heart of a lion, the strength of a bear, the speed of a cheetah, and the rotting head of a cheetah.

items.name: The Cheet Sheet
items.item_description: This cheetah-print skirt intimidates on the battlefield while allowing for freedom of movement. Let's be honest, it doesn't do a bad job of showing off those man-curves either.

items.name: The Tartantaloons
items.item_description: Are these Scottish pantaloons historically accurate? You got us. Why don't you go ask your boyfriend History?

items.name: The Steel Sixpack
items.item_description: This wrought-iron cuirass has been exactingly molded from the imaginary muscles you wish you had.

items.name: The Centurion
items.item_description: Unlike those cheap knock-offs, the brush part of THIS centurion helmet is made from the HEAD hair of your fallen enemies.

items.name: The Tartan Shade
items.item_description: This patterned cloak lets you skulk undetected in any plaid-covered shadows.

items.name: The Hardy Laurel
items.item_description: This bundle of spray painted sticks signified that you were a philosopher king in primitive cultures like Ancient Rome and present-day Canada. (Equips Romevision in Mann vs. Machine mode.)

items.name: The Brotherhood of Arms
items.item_description: Straight outta 2Fort.

items.name: The Well-Rounded Rifleman
items.item_description: The smooth lines of this versatile number will be instantly vaguely familiar to anyone who's ever seen a train conductor, been arrested in France, or fought in the U.S. Civil War.

items.name: The Breakneck Baggies
items.item_description: Combining the comfort of pajamas with the genital-concealing subterfuge of pants, these aerodynamic trackies will let your enemies know you're a man of mystery who probably got a good night's sleep.

items.name: The Powdered Practitioner
items.item_description: An integral part of any travel survival kit, this wig will help you escape Disney World if the Hall of Presidents ever comes to life. Comes with tri-corn hat in case Pirates of the Caribbean comes to life instead.

items.name: The Pocket Pyro
items.item_description: Loneliness is the world's deadliest silent killer. Next to carbon monoxide. But cuddle up to this adorable firebug, hold your breath, and you'll be free to concentrate on loud killers like car crashes and Freddy Krueger.

items.name: The Cloud Crasher
items.item_description: This paratrooper's helmet keeps your head safe while you jump out of planes. Show those birds who's boss! Teach some fluffy little clouds what they'll get if you ever catch them around your sky again!

items.name: The Pom-Pommed Provocateur
items.item_description: The thick woolen pom-pom stitched to the top of this ski mask is filled with poison, in case you are captured by people who want information on why you look ridiculous.

items.name: The Dark Age Defender
items.item_description: This knight's armor will repel anything someone from the 12th century might throw at you, be it a rock, a sword, a thatched cottage or a Merlin.

items.name: The Tyurtlenek
items.item_description: Around the skinny neck of an intellectual, jewel thief or Frenchman, a turtleneck tells people: "Please open-hand slap me in the face." On the iron frame of the Heavy, it says only: "I wear what I want."

items.name: The Mair Mask
items.item_description: Comes with a full can of MAIR, Mann Co.'s air substitute! One part nitrogen, no parts oxygen, NINE parts electrolytesMair gives regular air a kick in the pants for manly lungs on the go.

items.name: The Bigg Mann on Campus
items.item_description: "I should put a big red A on this thing for 'ALL SPORTS', cause that's my specialty."

items.name: The Cool Cat Cardigan
items.item_description: "Boom! Now I'm in the fifties! I look good in ANY decade!"

items.name: Greased Lightning
items.item_description: "I'm the only one on this team not balding! Damn right I'm gonna make my hair look good!"

items.name: The Red Army Robin
items.item_description: "Is tiny bird. Is adorable. TELL BIRD HE IS PRETTY!"

items.name: The Heavy-Weight Champ
items.item_description: "This belt tells babies that Heavy is champ. Big belt champ of all time."

items.name: The Tsarboosh
items.item_description: "Does little hat make Heavy's head look big? TELL TRUTH."

items.name: The Glasgow Great Helm
items.item_description: This knight's helm is perfect for defending against 12th century offensive weaponry, like swords, sticks and definitely-not-bullets.

items.name: The Caffeine Cooler
items.item_description: "Each canna Bonk's got four thousand percent of the daily caffeine a body needs, so you KNOW it's good for ya. And I drink 'em by the case, so I'm extra healthy."

items.name: The Half-Pipe Hurdler
items.item_description: "My moves are SICK, brother. Ask your girlfriend, cause she's been watchin'. Don't blame her, she's only human."

items.name: The Macho Mann
items.item_description: Sometimes it really does take a village, people.

items.name: The Trash Toter
items.item_description: "Waste not, want not, son."

items.name: The Dry Gulch Gulp
items.item_description: "When I'm hungry, I eat. When I'm thirsty, I drink. And when a man needs killin', I oblige him."

items.name: El Muchacho
items.item_description: Cosplay as a sleepy cowboy with this authentic 19th century sleeveless fleece snuggie.

items.name: The Backpack Broiler
items.item_description: I've got your back... steaks.

items.name: The Burning Bandana
items.item_description: Time to clean house.

items.name: The Soot Suit
items.item_description: Business up front. Ten deadly gallons of pressurized gas in the back.

items.name: The Hive Minder
items.item_description: The leading cause of death on the battlefield? You guessed it: Bee stings.

items.name: The Katyusha
items.item_description: "Heavy does not need plane to crush you. Only fists and hat."

items.name: Das Hazmattenhatten
items.item_description: "Breathing is agreeable to me, but sometimes there is air-stench. Now I laugh in the face of air. Thank you, this hat." (Description translated from German.)

items.name: Das Feelinbeterbager
items.item_description: "Hello, men of war! You will be dead soon. Here are pills." (Description translated from German.)

items.name: Das Ubersternmann
items.item_description: "You are not important but I am. My hat is a secret hat." (Description translated from German.)

items.name: Das Metalmeatencasen
items.item_description: "There is strength in your steel breast-blouse. Your chest meat is at ease." (Description translated from German.)

items.name: The Pardner's Pompadour
items.item_description: "It takes a hard man to tame this ten-gallon Texas hair tornado."

items.name: The Birdman of Australiacatraz
items.item_description: "Watch like an eagle. Strike like a hawk. Dance like no one's watching."

items.name: The Cobber Chameleon
items.item_description: "This little fellah's the perfect snipin' companion. He's quiet, he's camouflaged, and if you get hungry, you can eat 'im."

items.name: The Falconer
items.item_description: "This falconer's glove's perfect for snipin'. It's sturdy, it's comfortable, and if a falcon lands on it, you can eat 'im."

items.name: Graybanns
items.item_description: Gray Mann might be a heartless villain. But he DOES make some sweet sunglasses. Hate the player, not the game.

items.name: The Black Watch
items.item_description: This Scottish infantry tam o'shanter commemorates the desperately sober 5th battalion, who tried to make liquor out of gunpowder and accidentally invented stickybombs.

items.name: The Tartan Spartan
items.item_description: "Lads, tonight we DRINK IN HELL! And it's only noon right now, so let's ALSO DRINK RIGHT HERE!"

items.name: The Gaelic Golf Bag
items.item_description: "Ach, t'is a Cinderella story! Outta nowhere. A former demolitions expert, now, about to become the Masters champion. It looks like a mirac... It's in the hole! It's in the bloody hole!"

items.name: The Borscht Belt
items.item_description: "So many little pouches. Now Heavy can help carry your itty-bitty baby guns."

items.name: Das Naggenvatcher
items.item_description: "In the center of your head lives a skeleton. It is not enough! This hat is a head-skeleton for the outside." (Description translated from German.)

items.name: The Whiskey Bib
items.item_description: "Sometimes when yer swiggin' woodgrain alcohol from a clay jug, a wee bit can miss the mouth, like. Catch those precious drops with a genuine Scottish whiskey bib."

items.name: The Stormin' Norman
items.item_description: This knight's helm was painstakingly recreated using stills from the classic time travel episode (Ep 417: "A K.I.T.T. in King Arthur's Court") of the hit TV show Knight Rider.

items.name: The Flared Frontiersman
items.item_description: "I'll tell you what, these wide-bottom pants're slick as a whistle."

items.name: The Valley Forge
items.item_description: This tricorn is a tribute to our country's greatest President. The tiny medal on it is a tribute to the ribbony children's medal he won for inventing America.

items.name: The Compatriot
items.item_description: "This is not a bird, maggot! It is a shoulder-mounted symbol of freedom, and you WILL salute it in this man's army!"

items.name: The Caribbean Conqueror
items.item_description: "You! Stop jibbing that mainsail and give me twenty! You up in the crow's nest! Drop that telescope and get on your face! Everybody on this ship start doing push-ups!"

items.name: The Colonial Clogs
items.item_description: "I can confirm that these are George Washington's actual shoes, because I found them buried two feet up an Englishman's ass!"

items.name: The Whirly Warrior
items.item_description: "To your left, some French buildings. Directly in front of us is the Eiffel Tower, which I'm about to bring down. This concludes our helicopter tour of France."

items.name: The Federal Casemaker
items.item_description: "Men, if we are going to take down Al Capone, we will need to be in the FBI. Step one: These hats."

items.name: The Rebel Rouser
items.item_description: "Hold on, why are Americans fighting other Americans? Did everybody in France die and nobody told me?"

items.name: Das Maddendoktor
items.item_description: "My laughter is not borne from joy! I have birthed a devil! It is acceptable to me!" (Description translated from German.)

items.name: The Bear Necessities
items.item_description: "In Siberia, bear try to attack family. He try this once. Now he is little hat."

items.name: The Harmburg
items.item_description: "How do I look in this hat? On a scale of 'Handsome' to 'Extremely Handsome'."

items.name: The Gaelic Garb
items.item_description: "And we'll tell our enemies that they may take our lives, but they'll never take our FREEDOM! To wear these POOFY SHIRTS! What's that, Havish? Oh. AND THESE SASHES!"

items.name: The Rogue's Brogues
items.item_description: "Every day, I know I will be cutting something. Some days it is a rug. For those days, I have these shoes."

items.name: The Shogun's Shoulder Guard
items.item_description: "The next time some bleeding heart cries on your shoulder about the state of the environment, he can slam his tear ducts into the Shogun. This shoulder is CLOSED!"

items.name: Das Gutenkutteharen
items.item_description: "The hairs on your head-skin are physically attractive. Now we should have love relations." (Description translated from German.)

items.name: The Belgian Detective
items.item_description: "Inspector, seal the door! Someone in this room is a MURDERER!" [pause] "Me!" [stab stab stab stab stab]

items.name: The Hornblower
items.item_description: "This uniform was worn by Horatio Nelson during the Napoleonic Wars! If you sunk his ship he would swim at you with a cannon on his back! If he ran out of cannonballs he would fire himself at your hull! That is how bad he wanted to beat the French!"

items.name: Lieutenant Bites
items.item_description: Hobbies: contracting rabies, giving people rabies. Favorite foods: spoiled sour cream rations, arm meat.

items.name: The Brawling Buccaneer
items.item_description: "We do not plunder in this man's pirate army, maggot! On this ship you will patrol the seas for liberals and Communists, and go to bed at a sensible hour!"

items.name: The Blood Banker
items.item_description: "Oh, you'd like to make a deposit? Allow me to make one first. One knife. Into your back."

items.name: The After Dark
items.item_description: "Bartender. Scotch, neat. It has been a long day. Oh, is that a piano?" [sound of Chopin's Impromptu no. 4 in C sharp minor, ladies swooning]

items.name: The Delinquent's Down Vest
items.item_description: "Boom! Look how puffy this vest is, dummy! I sent the last one back. Not. Puffy. Enough."

items.name: Wet Works
items.item_description: "Rain: It's nature's Jarate. But it's not a drama: Keep the filthy stuff off yer noggin with this rubber hat."

items.name: Baron von Havenaplane
items.item_description: "Are you a plane-driver? I cannot tell because of your hat-disguise." (Description translated from German.)

items.name: Das Fantzipantzen
items.item_description: "Fancy men are beautiful but weak! You are a strong filthy idiot. Take what is rightfully yours!" (Description translated from German.)

items.name: The Bolshevik Biker
items.item_description: "I am riding to your tiny town."

items.name: The Pampered Pyro
items.item_description: Today, it's YOU Fortress. You deserve it.

items.name: The Virtual Viewfinder
items.item_description: Get a migraine for charity. (99 percent of community revenue goes to fund SpecialEffect, a charity working to help disabled players get back into the game.)

items.name: The Gabe Glasses
items.item_description: "These glasses help Heavy read sad stupid poem on your tombstone."

items.name: The Founding Father
items.item_description: This shirt envisions a terrifying alternate universe where our nation's patriots wore frilly-cuffed silk blouses instead of the respectable undershirts they possessed in actual history.

items.name: The Bone Dome
items.item_description: Comes with a visor capable of shielding your eyes from the harsh glare of people running away from you on fire.

items.name: The Air Raider

items.name: The Viking Braider
items.item_description: O.G. Vikings know: Braid before blade, son.

items.name: The Cuban Bristle Crisis

items.name: The Beep Boy
items.item_description: His facial expressions are synced to yours! Teach this Beep Boy how to be a Beep Man using nothing but the raw musky magnetism of your face.

items.name: Trickster's Turnout Gear
items.item_description: Trick your enemies into forgetting who set them on fire in the first place with this trustworthy-looking fireman's jacket.

items.name: The Gold Digger
items.item_description: Dag nab it before it's all sold out!

items.name: The Hurt Locher
items.item_description: Everyone likes to watch their enemies blow up. But if you're close enough to  get a really good look, you'll blow up too. It is life's greatest tragedy.

items.name: Li'l Snaggletooth
items.item_description: 'When I grow up, I want to be a hat.' -Li'l Snaggletooth
